# Week 6 / Day 1 — Merge Sort (Recursion)

## README.md

### Title

**Merge Sort — Recursion**

### Overview

This folder contains a recursive implementation of **Merge Sort**, an efficient, comparison-based, divide-and-conquer sorting algorithm. The goal of Day 1 is to: implement merge sort using recursion, explain the algorithm, and provide test cases and sample input/output suitable for a GitHub repository.

### Problem Statement

Given an array of integers, sort the array in non-decreasing order using Merge Sort (recursive approach).

### Algorithm (High level)

1. If the array has 0 or 1 element, it is already sorted — return.
2. Split the array into two halves (left and right).
3. Recursively sort both halves.
4. Merge the two sorted halves into a single sorted array.

### Time and Space Complexity

* **Time complexity:** O(n log n) in all cases (best, average, worst).
* **Space complexity:** O(n) auxiliary (for merging). Recursive call stack uses O(log n).

```bash
# compile
g++ -std=c++17 code/merge_sort.cpp -o merge_sort
# run
./merge_sort < examples/input1.txt
```

### Sample I/O (examples/input1.txt)

```
8
38 27 43 3 9 82 10 0
```

### Sample Output (examples/output1.txt)

```
0 3 9 10 27 38 43 82
```

### Notes

* This implementation emphasizes clarity and comments to help understanding recursion and merging.
* Optional: Add iterative/ bottom-up merge sort for comparison in future days.

---
```cpp
  #include<iostream>
#include<vector>
using namespace std;
void merge(vector<int> &arr,int st,int mid,int end){
    vector<int> temp;
    int i=st,j=mid+1;
    while(i<=mid && j<=end){
        if(arr[i]<=arr[j]){
            temp.push_back(arr[i]);
            i++;
        }
        else{
            temp.push_back(arr[j]);
            j++;
        }
    }
    while(i<=mid){
temp.push_back(arr[i]);
            i++;
    }
    while(j<=end){
        temp.push_back(arr[j]);
            j++;
    }
    for(int idx=0;idx<temp.size();idx++){
        arr[idx+st]=temp[idx];
    }
}
void mergeSort(vector<int> &arr,int st,int end){
   if(st<end){
     int mid=st+(end-st)/2;
    mergeSort(arr,st,mid-1);
    mergeSort(arr,mid+1,end);
    merge(arr,st,mid,end);
   }
}

int main(){
    vector<int> arr={12,31,35,8,32,17};
    mergeSort(arr,0,arr.size()-1);
    for(int val : arr){
        cout<< val <<" ";
    }
    cout<< endl;
    return 0;
}

